# ReaPrime / Decent.app — Project Rules

Read `AGENTS.md` at the repo root first. It is the canonical source for project conventions, hard rules, and deep reference routing.

## Top-Level Orientation

- `doc/AI_REPO_MAP.md` — fast file routing for any task.
- `AGENTS.md` — hard rules, naming, tracking, vocabulary.
- `CLAUDE.md` — `@AGENTS.md` + Claude-specific hooks.

## Domain-Specific Guidance (read when the task matches)

| When working on… | Read |
|------------------|------|
| BLE transport, connection lifecycle | `doc/AI_BLE_NOTES.md` |
| Build, platform, simulate | `doc/AI_BUILD_NOTES.md` |
| REST/WS API, auth proxy | `doc/AI_API_NOTES.md` |
| Database schema, migrations | `doc/AI_STORAGE_NOTES.md` |
| Crashes, telemetry, debugging | `doc/AI_DEBUG_NOTES.md` |
| Tests, widget patterns, mocks | `doc/AI_TESTING_NOTES.md` |
| API reference | `doc/Api.md`, `assets/api/rest_v1.yml`, `assets/api/websocket_v1.yml` |
| Skins, plugins, profiles | `doc/Skins.md`, `doc/Plugins.md`, `doc/Profiles.md` |
| Device management | `doc/DeviceManagement.md` |
| Release process | `doc/RELEASE.md` |

## Key Conventions

- Test-first: `flutter test` + `flutter analyze` before commit.
- Update API specs in the same commit as endpoint changes.
- Never import BLE libraries outside `lib/src/services/ble/`.
- All BLE operations use 128-bit UUID.
- Constructor DI — no service locators.
- `main` is protected; push via PR only.
